The paper deals with multi-agent planning, which is a topic that falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also involves the use of temporal logic specifications for behavior and tasks, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper proposes a decentralized approach to planning, which is a topic in programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). Finally, the paper deals with motion planning, which is a topic in robotics (cs.RO).
